HEADWORD: heartbeat
<hw>heartbeat</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the audible and palpable rhythmic
contraction and expansion of the arteries with each beat of the heart;
<as>as, he listened to her <ex>heartbeat</ex> with a
stethoscope</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> pulse, pulsation, beat.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>in a heartbeat</b></col> <cd>immediately.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

